traits.name: Volcanic
traits.description: A volatile world marked by intense volcanic activity, creating a hazardous environment with the potential for valuable resource extraction, such as rare metals and geothermal energy.

traits.name: Frozen
traits.description: An ice-covered world with frigid temperatures, providing unique research opportunities and resources such as ice water, ammonia ice, and other frozen compounds.

traits.name: Jungle
traits.description: A lush, tropical world with dense vegetation and a thriving ecosystem, offering a wealth of resources and unique opportunities for research and exploration.

traits.name: Barren
traits.description: A desolate world with little to no vegetation or water, presenting unique challenges for habitation and resource extraction.

traits.name: Ocean
traits.description: A world dominated by vast, interconnected bodies of water, presenting unique challenges for habitation and resource extraction while supporting a diverse array of marine life.

traits.name: Sprawling Cities
traits.description: Expansive urban centers that stretch across the landscape, boasting advanced infrastructure and diverse populations.

traits.name: Bureaucratic
traits.description: A waypoint governed by complex regulations, red tape, and layers of administration, often leading to inefficiencies and frustration.

traits.name: Industrial
traits.description: A waypoint dominated by factories, refineries, and other heavy industries, often accompanied by pollution and a bustling workforce.

traits.name: Marketplace
traits.description: A thriving center of commerce where traders from across the galaxy gather to buy, sell, and exchange goods.
